Hackathon submission: http://hackbu-2015s.challengepost.com/submissions/34578-dirpl

Dependencies: dirpl should work on any Unix system with python 3 installed.

To get started, run fact.sh.
This will create a program with the following structure that calculates 
the factorial of 5.
The program can be executed by running "./dirpl program/"

program/
├── a
│   └── fact()
│       └── a
│           └── 5
└── :fact_n
    └── ifelse()
        ├── a
        │   └── <=
        │       ├── a
        │       │   └── n
        │       └── b
        │           └── 1
        ├── b
        │   └── 1
        └── c
            └── *
                ├── a
                │   └── n
                └── b
                    └── fact()
                        └── a
                            └── -
                                ├── a
                                │   └── n
                                └── b
                                    └── 1
